as discussed in the SRE planning for Q3 on 6th of June 2017 we need this mechanism to stop / start our dev & test - infrastructure during nights / weekends:

* stop instances
* stop RDS
* resize autoscaling groups to 0

# commands

two new kumo commands to use this feature:

* `kumo stop`
* `kumo start`

# configuration

Add optional attribute `DisableStop` so we can prevent parts of our infrastructure from this in case the application is not yet ready for it.

```bash
{
  "kumo": {
    "stack": {
      "StackName": "gcdt-sample-stack"
    }
    "parameters": {
      "VPCId": "lookup:stack:<stack-name>:DefaultVPCId",
      "ScaleMinCapacity": "1",
      "ScaleMaxCapacity": "1",
      "InstanceType": "t2.micro",
      "DefaultInstancePolicyARN": "lookup:stack:<stack-name>:DefaultInstancePolicyARN",
      "AMI": "lookup:baseami"
    }
    "deployment": {
      "DisableStop": true
    }
  }
}
```

